thrombosis in a 38-year-old woman. <b>(a)</b> Venograms show an occlusion (arrow) of the right iliac vein and development of collateral vessels (arrowheads) around the occluded vein. <b>(b)</b> Axial CT image shows a low-attenuation thrombus (arrow) in the right common iliac vein.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.e31&amp;id=F11A">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="F11B" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.e31/asset/images/e31f11b.jpeg" height="1085" width="1280" aria-labelledby="F11B" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><b>Figure 11b.</b>  Deep vein thrombosis in a 38-year-old woman. <b>(a)</b> Venograms show an occlusion (arrow) of the right iliac vein and development of collateral vessels (arrowheads) around the occluded vein. <b>(b)</b> Axial CT image shows a low-attenuation thrombus (arrow) in the right common iliac vein.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.e31&amp;id=F11B">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="F12A" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.e31/asset/images/e31f12a.jpeg" height="1095" width="1280" aria-labelledby="F12A" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><b>Figure 12a.</b>  Occlusion of the IVC and hepatic and renal veins in a 38-year-old man. <b>(a, b)</b> CT images show low-attenuation filling defects (arrow in <b>a</b>) in the left hepatic vein, the IVC, and the left renal vein (arrowheads in <b>b</b>), indicating thrombotic occlusion. <b>(c)</b> Follow-up CT image obtained 1 year later shows infarction (*) in the left hepatic lobe.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.e31&amp;id=F12A">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcapti